summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 1731 entitled: "An ordinance granting to Norval H. Latimer, John P. Hoyt, and Watson C. Squire, the privilege of extending electric wires from what is known as the Squire- Latimer Building, at the City of Seattle, to other buildings at the request of or by the agreement with the owners thereof, and to cross and use the intervening streets and alleys for that purpose" approved May 18, 1891.
